article.headline: Bryant downs Sacred Heart, 76-67
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- Dyami Starks scored 22 points to lead three Bryant players with 20-plus points as the Bulldogs beat Sacred Heart 76-67 on Sunday. Corey Maynard and Alex Francis had 20 points for Bryant (14-9, 6-2 Northeast Conference). Francis had eight rebounds and Starks made all three of Bryant's 3-pointers, despite 18 team attempts. Louis Montes scored 22 points, including four 3-pointers, for Sacred Heart (4-19, 1-7). Steve Glowiak added 21 points on seven 3-pointers, six in the second half. Montes and Glowiak combined to make 11 of 20 shots from beyond the arc. Bryant built a 41-23 advantage, but Glowiak's 3-pointer made it a five-point game with 2:06 left. Maynard answered with a layup and Starks' 3-pointer pushed Bryant's lead to eight points with 39 seconds left.
